	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi Jinfox.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'll try to help as best I can, but the question of whether or not you should make another Paladin is really one that you can only answer yourself.<br><br>In the time you've played, what aspects of grouping have you found most enjoyable?  Not knowing what your other characters are, I can't say whether or not you've tried all aspects...  Do you like to Tank, Pull, Nuke?  Some combination thereof?<br><br>The Paladin can fill many roles in a group, and can solo effectively, especially against undead.  This makes them quite versatile.<br><br>As far as races go, the High Elf is my preferred choice.  The high base wisdom and charisma provided by the race suit a Paladin well.  This of course comes at a price of strength.  You'll find that a full suit of armor brings you very close to your weight limit.  Unless you spend as many ability points as possible on strength when you create the character.  I recommend against this as you will still be weaker than most other warriors and a higher wis/chr/dex/agi will help you more than strength.  Good night vision is a plus also as many of the undead you will fight are found in dark places.<br><br>I know this is not much but I hope it helps.  Perhaps if you provide more information on what you have and what you like, myself and others can give you better advice on what to play.  =)<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
