	   <tr><td colspan=2>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Velium weapons are essentially the same as fine steel weapons, with a proc that does about 12 damage of cold magic.  It will start working at level 24, I believe.<br><br>2.  That <i>is</i> the entire premise of a paladin.  You have the AC and HP to be one group's main tank, while later in the day you could be a different group's main healer.<br><br>You can also secondary tank adds and backup heal, or do some crowd controlling, or do AC buffs to save your cleric's mana.  You have absolutely superb versatility in groups and can fill almost any role in a pinch.<br><br>Some spells I would suggest as absolute essentials are:<br><br>Level 9<br>Minor Healing<br>Courage<br>Cure Poison<br>Spook the Dead<br>Cease<br><br>Level 15<br>Light Healing<br>Holy Armor<br>Cure Disease<br>Ward Undead<br>Desist<br><br>Level 22<br>Center<br>Invigor<br>Root<br>Invisibility versus Undead<br><br>Level 30<br>Healing<br>Stun<br>Endure Magic<br>Expulse Undead<br>Spirit Armor<br>Symbol of Transal<br>Instrument of Nife<br><br>Level 39<br>Greater Healing<br>Guard<br>Cancel Magic<br>Daring<br>Counteract Poison<br>Symbol of Ryltan<br>Divine Vigor<br><br>Level 49<br>Armor of Faith<br>Dismiss Undead<br>Holy Might<br>Valor<br>Revive<br>Symbol of Pinzarn<br>Divine Might<br>Valor of Marr<br><br>Level 50+<br>Force<br>Enstill<br>Expel Undead<br>Quellious' Words of Tranquility<br>Resist Magic<br>Divine Aura<br>Wave of Healing<br>Counteract Disease<br>Breath of Tunare<br>Superior Healing<br>Nullify Magic<br>Symbol of Naltron<br>Healing Wave of Prexus<br>Resurrection<br>Celestial Cleansing<br>Shield of Words<br>Resolution<br>Yaulp IV<br>Brell's Mountainous Barrier<br><br>You can find a description of all these spells here:  <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon/spells/spells.asp?Class=Paladin" target=_new>http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon/spells/spells.asp?Class=Paladin</a><br><br>3.  Groups look for people who know their class, and well.   You need to be smart, and you need to be aware of what's going around you.  You have to know the zone you're in if you want to do well.  You need to know when to take heat off the main tank, when to not get hit, and when to BE the main tank.  You need to know what spells to have loaded given the situation.<br><br>Be fun to be around, don't be an ass.  Get to know people with similar play styles and you'll never have trouble getting a group.<br><br>G'luck.<br>&nbsp;<br><b>Praetor</b>, 60th Crusader<br>Avatars of Discord</td></tr>
