	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK..hope this helps you out a bit=)<br><br>1. Velium Weapons are all magical weapons w/a proc of Velium Shards some have it and some dont.&nbsp;&nbsp;The only velium type weapon i have is called Iceforge Shackles which has a right clickable proc of 12dd proc max.  I have never used any velious type weapons that allowed me to proc below 35+.  As far as that I cannot tell you much about it since most of the weapons I use are pre-velious.<br><br>2. What's good about a Paladin???  Hmmm...they're tanks and they can heal themselves=P  J/K but pretty much is the truth.  I used to be a cleric on a friend's account before I started playing EQ regularly.  I found that cleric are not good tanks and that I really like to fight, but be able to heal myself.  Paladin seemed to be the best choice.  Lay of Hands is a great skill to have especially now w/Luclin expansion its a Complete Heal.  Can be used every 1hr.  As far as spells are concerned I like them all=)  Heal, stuns, buffs, extra damage spells vs. undead are all handy in battle type situations.  I like paladins since I can do alot of things other melees cant.  I can heal myself after soloing, buff myself, grab aggro off casting casters by stunning and taunting off mobs or even rooting mobs if the going gets tough.  A paladin is great in dungeons like Lguk or Unrest especially with Invis vs. Undead.  I can heal in mid/after battles, I can grab aggro like a warrior and nuke undead w/undead DD spells.  Personally I think Paladins are great especially at higher levels.  I am currently 50 and loving it.  The class that you pick should be the class that best fits your needs and your style of gameplay.  I like to tank and heal and have magic spells...pretty much why I like paladins=)  Downfall to a paladin vs. pure melee is meditating for mana if you have no healer, but that's when an enchanter comes in to clarity or breeze you so you can gain mana much faster=P<br><br>3. As far as grouping w/a paladin.  I've never have problems finding groups.  A paladin can fit in almost any type of groups, Lguk especially.  I'm either main or secondary tank and back up healer in case cleric is out of mana.  At lvl 45 you can proc your Deepwater Helm and this can be used to heal after battles especially when soloing.  Unlimited proc of Daring spell which is a buff/heal type spell.  At lvl 39 you get a self regen spell called Divine Purpose, at 49 you get a self-haste called Valor of Marr...the possibilities are endless and there's more to look forward to=)<br><br> <br>&nbsp;<br>Furyon<br>59 Knight<br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=605752" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=605752</a><br><br>Karana Server<br><br><br></td></tr>
