	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Fellow Paladins,<br><br>Thought I would pass on my experience getting the Bracer of Benevolence last night for anyone contemplating this item.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Bracer is part of the Commander Leuz Task Quest from Skyshrine.  The Bracer is very nice:<br><br>17 AC, +8 Str, +8 Sta, +12 sv Cold, +12 sv Magic, +5 sv Fire, +30 hps<br><br>The Quest is well explained in the Quest section of this site. Scout Charissa is on CoV faction and regarded me as an Ally.<br><br>I handed in the Scout's Tools to her which spawned the Giants and the Captain.  A level 60 Druid Harmony Pulled the Captain alone and brought him to the Siren's Grotto tunnel entrance.  We had no KoS to CoV Faction people in our group so there were no adds, although several mobs wandered past during the fight.<br><br>The Captain is TOUGH!! He has lots of hit pts and hits in the mid-200's.  He cannot be slowed so make sure you have serious healing power to back you up. We only used one group that consisted of:<br><br>60 Warrior<br>60 Druid<br>60 Cleric<br>60 Enchanter<br>55 Necromancer<br>54 Paladin (ME!)<br><br>The battle took quite a while, but there was no real danger to anyone. Druid pulled Giant, Warrior tanked him for 15 seconds, called assist, I began attacking from behind to avoid the Ripostes and Dodges. I never drew aggro during the entire battle.  <br><br>Cleric used Complete Heal at 40% health on Warrior.  Rinse and Repeat until finally dead.  The Cleric did go OOM before the battle was over, hence the reason for the Necromancer...along with his nice pet.  Necromancer gave Mana to the Cleric to continue the final part of the battle.<br><br>I looted the sprocket looking drop he had (Only item he had), turned it into Scout Charissa and got the Robe. Turned the Robe in for the Bracer.<br><br>All in all, in went along without a hitch. Good Luck!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot;<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
