	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 15th 1:34 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.93]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As long as agility is over 75 you're fine.&nbsp;&nbsp;Above that it doesn't help too much.  So yes, 70 agility is not such a good thing.  And if you happen to get encumbered the problem will be even worse.  <br><br>I was wearing mostly banded even up till around 22 so I think your armor is fine.  <br><br>At level 12 it's a toss up whether or not to start over.  If you created a new character with better stats and handed over your existing armor and equipment, you could easily get five levels in a couple hours and probably be back to twelve in a couple days max.  The choice is up to you.  Knowing what I know now it would probably take me five or six hours max to get to twelve.<br><br>At low levels, agility items can be pretty scarce so that's a factor as well.  You might not be able to overcome the problem until your mid-twenties or so.  And even then, you may be put in situations where you sacrifice AC or other stats to keep your agility up.  Being a weak high elf paladin, I make this trade off routinely with str items.  (I do it to avoid encumbrance, I know that str has little impact on dmg).   <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
