	   <a name=10083724785554></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10083724785554><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=10083724785554>RE: Need the names of the new stuns</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=10083724785554#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=83710><span id=Scholar>jcasetnl</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>153 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Dec 14th 6:27 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just to clarify, these aren't zero-duration stuns.&nbsp;&nbsp;I know I know, the duration is so short it almost seems like they are but I'm not just splitting hairs.  <br><br>One effective use for these stuns (other than caster interuption, which is their primary use) is in groups without a sow'd puller (or fast as or faster than sow mobs).  Hit your assist social to target the bad guy a ways out and then cast cease.  This will cause the bad guy who's likely smacking the back of your puller's head to stop just long enough to be out of range.  At the same time, if you're tanking, you've just generated some agro and holding it will be a tad easier.  <br><br>I found that after just after one stun if I stood in the path of the mob it would attack me instead of following the puller.  So between that and the dmg we reduced by seperating them I was saving the warrior about 100-150 hp on average.  Not bad for a 15 mana stun.<br><br>Of course, if you're puller does remember to bring his bow, most of this is moot.  :-)  And if the mob is within spell casting range, it's also moot.<br><br>An alternative is to use root, which has the primary disadvantage of sometimes stopping the mob within agro range of other mobs, when the idea of pulling in most cases is to single out one or more mobs to more easily dispatch them.  <br><br>And finally against pulls of casters, the caster will ussually stop at some point to cast and you can get in a stun there to interupt.  <br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Dec 14 18:33:35 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
